# .rules

## General Project Rules

- This is a static GitHub Pages project.
- Keep everything simple.
- Prefer HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Bootstrap.
- Do not introduce backend.
- Do not add database.
- Do not add login/register.
- Do not add build tools.
- Do not require npm install.
- Do not break existing pages.

## Course Creation Rules

When the user asks to create a course, the AI must:

1. Create course folder.
2. Create course overview page.
3. Split theory content into lessons.
4. Create lesson pages.
5. Create sidebar or table of contents.
6. Create quiz JavaScript.
7. Create essay self-study section.
8. Create suggested answers.
9. Add previous/next lesson navigation.
10. Update `index.html` with the new course.
11. Update `courses.html` if it exists.
12. Ensure responsive layout.

## Do Not Stop At Text

When creating a course, do not only write course content in the chat.

The AI must create or modify project files.

## Required Lesson Sections

Every lesson must include:

```txt
Video mô phỏng
Tài liệu lý thuyết
Ví dụ minh họa
Trắc nghiệm
Câu hỏi tự luận
Đáp án tham khảo
```

## Homepage Rules

When adding a course, update `index.html`.

If `index.html` has a course section, add the new course there.

If `index.html` does not have a course section, create a course section.

The new course entry must link to:

```txt
courses/<course-slug>/index.html
```

## Navigation Rules

Every course must include navigation.

Course overview page:

- Link to homepage
- Link to lessons
- Link to courses page if available

Lesson page:

- Link to homepage
- Link to course overview
- Link to all lessons in sidebar
- Link to previous lesson
- Link to next lesson

## Responsive Rules

Use Bootstrap responsive classes.

Desktop/laptop:

- Sidebar on the left
- Lesson content on the right

Mobile:

- Sidebar above the content or collapsible
- No horizontal scrolling
- Buttons must be easy to tap

## Content Rules

- User-facing content should be Vietnamese.
- File and folder names should be English.
- Explain concepts clearly.
- Use beginner-friendly examples.
- Avoid overly long paragraphs.
- Use lists and tables where helpful.

## Quiz Rules

- Use JavaScript.
- Show score immediately.
- Do not send data to a server.
- Do not require account.
- Use 3 to 5 questions per lesson when possible.

## Essay Rules

- Essay questions are self-study only.
- Do not grade essays.
- Suggested answer must be available.
- Suggested answer should be hidden by default.
- Learners can compare their answer manually.

## File Naming Rules

Use lowercase and hyphenated names.

Good examples:

```txt
agent-engineering
python-fundamentals
data-structures
lesson-01.html
binary-search.html
what-is-ai-agent.html
```

Bad examples:

```txt
Agent Engineering
Bai 1.html
Lesson 01.html
finalVersion.html
```

## Path Rules

Use relative paths.

Do not use local absolute paths like:

```txt
C:\Users\...
/home/user/...
```

Do not use root-relative paths like:

```txt
/assets/css/style.css
```

unless the project is specifically configured for that.

## Safety Rules

- Do not store API keys.
- Do not store passwords.
- Do not include private user data.
- Do not use external paid services by default.
